The '''Dalsfjord Lighthouse Museum''' ({{lang-no|Dalsfjord fyrmuseum}}) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] museum dedicated to documenting and presenting the social history of the people that built [[lighthouse]]s, [[sector light]]s, markers, moorings, and [[port]]s along the [[Norwegian coastline]].<ref name="Sunnmore">{{cite web|title=Dalsfjord Fyrmuseum, Volda|url=http://www.sunnmore.museum.no/musea/dalsfjord-fyrmuseum/|website=Stiftinga Sunnmøre Museum|accessdate=January 28, 2018}}</ref>
The museum is located in [[Dravlaus]] in the municipality of [[Volda]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Fyrhistorie|url=http://www.ullanett.com/ullafyr.fyrhistorie.html|website=Ulla|accessdate=January 28, 2018}}</ref> and it is part of the [[Sunnmøre Museum Foundation]].<ref name="Sunnmore"/><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hjemdahl|first1=Anne-Sofie|title=Stiftelsen Sunnmøre museum|url=https://snl.no/Stiftelsen_Sunnm%C3%B8re_museum|website=Store norske leksikon|accessdate=January 28, 2018}}</ref> The museum was opened in a new location with a new exhibit on November 8, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dalsfjorden fyrmuseum i nye lokale|url=http://kystverket.no/Nyheter/2012/November/Dalsfjorden-fyrmuseum-i-nye-lokale/|website=Kystverket|accessdate=January 28, 2018|date=November 9, 2012}}</ref>
